frameDefinitions: This frame describes intentionally formed human social groups (here termed Organizations) with some definite structure and Members.
A Text is an entity that contains linguistic, symbolic information on a Topic, created by an Author at the Time_of_creation.
A Speaker warns an Addressee by giving a Message that describes an undesirable situation that may affect the Addressee.
In this frame, an Agent engages in personal body care by grooming either a Patient or a Body_part.
Some Stimulus causes a Cognizer to think of a prior Phenomenon due to its perceived similarity.
These are words referring to control by a Leader over a particular entity  or group (the Governed) or an Activity.
frameExamples: Jackson <t>warned</t> me that the weather could change quickly, but I guess I didn't really believe him.
I burned down the malt shop where we used to go just because it <t>reminds</t> me of you
Sebek em hat was a <t>Leader</t> of Priests. ca. 1780 BC
listRoleDefinitions: The entity of which the individuals are <fen>Members</fen>.
A person belonging to an <fen>Organization</fen>.
This role describes the general location where the <fen>Organization</fen> operates, but does not indicate the possessor of the <fen>Organization</fen>.
The <fen>Text</fen> is the entity that contains linguistic information. This an incorporated role for each LU in this frame.
The region where the <fen>Text</fen> is sold, circulated, or otherwise popular.
The <fen>Speaker</fen> produces the <fen>Message</fen> to alert the <fen>Addressee</fen> as to possible danger.
The <fen>Addressee</fen> receives the warning from the <fen>Speaker</fen>.
The <fen>Message</fen> is the communication produced by the <fen>Speaker</fen>.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is a general description of the content of the <fen>Message</fen>.
This frame element is the <fen>Medium</fen> in which the <fen>Message</fen> is expressed.
The time period during which the <fen>Speaker</fen> warns the <fen>Addressee</fen>.
The location in which the <fen>Speaker</fen> warns <fen>Addressee</fen>.
The agent is the person who does the grooming.
The patient is the person who gets washed.
This is the region of the body that gets groomed.
This role identifies the time when the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The <fen>Cognizer</fen> is the person who remembers the <fen>Phenomenon</fen> .
The <fen>Phenomenon</fen> is the mental content that a <fen>Cognizer</fen> remembers.
The entity or situation that causes the <fen>Cognizer</fen> to think of the <fen>Phenomenon</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the Cognizer remembers the <fen>Phenomenon</fen>.

The <fen>Leader</fen> is the one who has the role of leading.  With verbs, and with predicate nominals linking an individual to a <fen>Role</fen>, the <fen>Leader</fen> is usually the External Argument:

The role played by the <fen>Leader</fen> in a given situation, often an official title; incorporated in most noun LUsin this frame. When expressed separately from the target, <fen>Role</fen> usually occurs in a PP Complement headed by <ment>as</ment>.
The entity whose actions or beliefs the <fen>Leader</fen> directs in the context of a joint activity or movement.  This entity can be a political body, a person, or a group of people.
The <fen>Leader</fen> directs the <fen>Activity</fen>.
<fen>Time</fen> refers to the point in time that the leadership took place.
The locale from which the <fen>Leader</fen> leads the <fen>Governed</fen> or the <fen>Activity</fen>.
listRoleExamples: <fex>Bill</fex> warned me that he would come to the party.
When did you warn <fex>everyone</fex> about the virus?
The authorities warned me <fex>that my brother had been arrested</fex>.
Leroy warned his coworkers <fex>about the upcoming audit</fex>.
The city will now warn residents <fex>in text messages and emails</fex>.
They warned me <fex>right away</fex> and everything worked out great.
She was warned about it <fex>in front of her family</fex>, but it seemed to have no effect.
You remind me <fex>of my uncle Jerry</fex>
<fex>Internationalization</fex> conjures up a world of diplomatic exchanges and international agencies in which the interests of ex-colonial and great powers still linger
The general led his troops into battle <fex>on June 22, 1883</fex>.
He ruled the west <fex>from his palace in Milan</fex>.
